01:21.123 --> 01:22.748
And go into real estate.

01:22.792 --> 01:23.957
- In this market?
[pop]

01:24.043 --> 01:26.585
Ah! I can't take these booms!

01:26.670 --> 01:30.130
Make them stop!
I can't live in here forever.

01:30.174 --> 01:32.633
I'm running out of
underwear crotches to eat.

01:32.718 --> 01:33.967
[growls]

01:34.053 --> 01:35.552
- Chief, I really need
a break

01:35.596 --> 01:37.221
From dealing with
everyone's problems.

01:37.264 --> 01:39.932
If you're so scared,
just go hang out with jill.

01:39.975 --> 01:43.185
- I'm so scared,
I don't know who jill is!

01:43.270 --> 01:45.104
- Bye, kiddoes!
- Who the hell is that?

01:45.189 --> 01:48.482
- I'm off to my "1619 project"
listening and nodding party.

01:48.567 --> 01:51.652
- [gasps] she can't leave!
Honey, do something!

01:51.737 --> 01:53.737
- Why is it always my job
to do something?

01:53.823 --> 01:54.988
[both growling]
- oh, no.

01:55.074 --> 01:56.448
You two seem very upset.

01:56.492 --> 01:59.159
- We're fine!
- I have conflicting feelings

01:59.245 --> 02:02.162
About medicating you, but the
thundershirt isn't helping,

02:02.206 --> 02:04.498
And I kept the thunderpants
for myself.

02:05.709 --> 02:06.875
[fireworks continue popping]

02:06.919 --> 02:09.211
- Oh, my god!
Honey, do something!

02:09.296 --> 02:12.214
- Could you just handle
something on your own?

02:12.299 --> 02:15.926
I'm so sick...Of everyone
else's [mutters] problems.

02:16.053 --> 02:19.054
- Fine.
I can handle this on my own.

02:19.140 --> 02:21.932
[slurring] I can do
anything I put my...

02:22.017 --> 02:23.767
[voice distorting]
mind to...

02:23.853 --> 02:26.728
I mean, it's supposed to be
a government of the animals,

02:26.814 --> 02:29.189
By the animals, for the...

02:29.275 --> 02:32.151
Oh, don't help me--
animals?

02:32.194 --> 02:33.944
So I'm gonna take matters
into my own paws,

02:34.029 --> 02:35.445
Get rid of the booms,

02:35.489 --> 02:38.907
<i> And make the world</i>
<i> a better place for all of us.</i>

02:38.951 --> 02:40.909
That means you, pal.

02:40.995 --> 02:43.704
- Thanks,<i> pal.</i>
- It's my pleasure.

02:43.789 --> 02:46.081
We will all benefit
from my naiveite

02:46.167 --> 02:48.625
And misplaced optimism.

02:49.920 --> 02:53.422
I'm here to make
my mark on washington.

02:54.091 --> 02:55.549
Hey, senator mcturtle.

02:55.593 --> 02:58.760
Big boom has been terrorizing
us animals for decades,

02:58.888 --> 03:00.095
And it has to stop.

03:00.181 --> 03:02.347
So I went to the place
where things get done--

03:02.433 --> 03:05.809
Social media--but said some
things that got me kicked off,

03:05.853 --> 03:07.269
So now I'm here.

03:07.313 --> 03:09.021
Will you help me?
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

03:09.106 --> 03:10.480
What's your name, son?

03:10.566 --> 03:13.984
- Chief, but you can call me
chiefy, chief baby,

03:14.028 --> 03:16.278
Or @mrfloofypants.

03:16.322 --> 03:18.989
- Well, chiefy,
while I admire your gumption,

03:19.033 --> 03:20.774
That's not my committee.

03:20.784 --> 03:22.451
But just inside that building

03:22.494 --> 03:25.412
Are countless senators
who would be more than happy

03:25.456 --> 03:27.831
To help a courageous
canine like you.

03:27.875 --> 03:30.542
All you have to do
is knock on their doors.

03:30.586 --> 03:33.003
Good luck, and dogspeed.

03:34.131 --> 03:36.840
[beep]
I need you to keep your eye

03:36.926 --> 03:38.884
On a dog named chief.

03:38.928 --> 03:42.596
He's digging around
where he doesn't belong.

03:42.681 --> 03:44.097
And when he's done with that,

03:44.141 --> 03:47.059
I think he's going to do
some investigating.

03:47.895 --> 03:50.687
[fireworks continue popping]
- [giggling]

03:50.773 --> 03:54.650
- [whimpers] sick of dealing
with everyone else's problems.

03:54.735 --> 03:56.068
<i> Problems...Problems...</i>

03:56.153 --> 03:58.737
[car horn honks]
[groans] ohh...

03:58.781 --> 04:02.032
Oh! It's already
quarter past sunrise o'clock!

04:02.117 --> 04:04.493
[car horn honking]
hold on, be right there.

04:04.578 --> 04:06.286
[grunting]

04:06.372 --> 04:09.581
Ooh! I gotta lay off
those late-night squirrels.

04:13.087 --> 04:15.545
- You didn't tell me
you were goin' out.

04:15.631 --> 04:17.130
- I didn't know I had to.

04:17.174 --> 04:21.009
- You get your butt
back here, honey--now!

04:21.095 --> 04:22.928
- Sorry, chief.
Don't wait up!

04:23.013 --> 04:24.721
- Don't you tell me not--

04:24.765 --> 04:27.808
[snoring]

04:27.893 --> 04:29.518
- Let's go, let's go!

04:29.645 --> 04:31.228
- Relaxicon, here we come!

04:31.272 --> 04:33.146
- North america's
second-largest

04:33.232 --> 04:35.649
Boom-free relaxation
festival!

04:35.693 --> 04:38.235
- And a break from fixing
everyone's problems.

04:38.320 --> 04:40.153
- Before we know it,
we'll be up to

04:40.239 --> 04:43.156
Our exposed anuses
in cucumber water.

04:43.284 --> 04:44.992
- Wait, wait, this is my dream.
I wanna drive.

04:45.119 --> 04:47.119
- [sighs] fine.
- Ow!

04:47.204 --> 04:48.829
- Sorry. I'm not used to legs.

04:48.872 --> 04:51.039
- Road trip!
[static]

04:51.083 --> 04:53.583
- Say "no booms!"
- no booms!

04:53.669 --> 04:55.043
[click]

04:55.087 --> 04:58.046
Two dogs, 12 teats,
no rules!

