Is there for national
emergencies only!

12:21.032 --> 12:23.700
- Like what, a jelly nato?

12:23.785 --> 12:25.034
[laughter]

12:25.120 --> 12:27.537
- Order!
- There will be no order

12:27.664 --> 12:31.541
Until you put a stop
to this hypocrisy, man!

12:31.626 --> 12:33.752
[cheering, whooping]

12:33.795 --> 12:34.836
- Order!
- Yeah!

12:34.871 --> 12:36.880
- Order! All right, that's it.

12:36.965 --> 12:39.257
We're adjourning for lunch.

12:43.430 --> 12:44.679
- I am starving.

12:44.723 --> 12:47.173
I'll buy us snacks.
- I don't have any money.

12:47.184 --> 12:49.601
Maybe that's because it's
a concept I don't understand.

12:49.686 --> 12:52.562
I mean, a currency backed by
a mutual agreement of value?

12:52.647 --> 12:54.898
That doesn't make sense.
- Leave this to me.

12:54.941 --> 12:57.358
[bell jingles]

12:59.196 --> 13:02.989
Hello. Can I please have
a pack of catnip?

13:03.033 --> 13:05.575
- Sure can,
now that it's legal.

13:05.619 --> 13:07.035
- Meow!
- Nice and easy,

13:07.120 --> 13:09.287
And no one gets squirt.

13:09.331 --> 13:11.790
Hey, abs, grab those bags
of kibble for me.

13:11.875 --> 13:12.916
- Uh, okay.

13:12.959 --> 13:15.293
And I don't love
the objectification,

13:15.337 --> 13:17.295
But I do appreciate
the compliment.

13:17.380 --> 13:19.714
- And you are going to
give me all of your cash.

13:19.800 --> 13:21.382
And you're going to start
counting

13:21.468 --> 13:24.719
And not call the cops
until you get to 100.

13:24.763 --> 13:27.597
- Okay. One, two,

13:27.682 --> 13:30.058
Um, I wanna say tomato?

13:30.101 --> 13:31.768
- Three!
- I dunno.

13:31.853 --> 13:33.686
I'm pretty sure it's tomato.

13:33.730 --> 13:35.104
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

13:35.190 --> 13:39.067
- Get in!
Drive, drive, drive!

13:41.154 --> 13:43.905
<i> - So now I'm implicated</i>

13:43.949 --> 13:45.573
In an assault
on a police officer,

13:45.617 --> 13:46.991
Robbing a convenience store,

13:47.035 --> 13:49.285
And we're adding a sexy cat
to our crew?

13:49.371 --> 13:52.664
- I gotta say, I liked your
moves back at that minimart.

13:52.699 --> 13:53.873
- Yeah, you did.

13:53.875 --> 13:55.750
- But I would have done it
differently.

13:55.794 --> 13:57.502
I take pride
in being courteous.

13:57.587 --> 13:59.754
- So what do you do?
- It goes a little

13:59.756 --> 14:01.548
Something like this.

14:01.633 --> 14:03.424
All right, cats and dogs,

14:03.468 --> 14:06.678
Let's see who'll win the prize
for keepin' their cool.

14:06.763 --> 14:10.515
This squirt gun is loaded,
but if nobody gets upset,

14:10.559 --> 14:12.517
Nobody gets wet.

14:12.602 --> 14:14.435
Aah!
[dryer humming]

14:14.479 --> 14:15.937
[both laughing]

14:16.022 --> 14:18.064
- Okay, that was fun.
Now get out.

14:18.108 --> 14:20.859
- Well, thank you both
for a lovely evening.

14:20.902 --> 14:22.235
[bags rustle]

14:25.115 --> 14:27.615
- I finally find a cat
who isn't terrified of me,

14:27.701 --> 14:29.075
And you kick him out?

14:29.160 --> 14:31.911
- If you hadn't gotten us
this kibble, you'd be out too.

14:31.913 --> 14:33.121
Wait--where is it?
- What?

14:33.164 --> 14:34.914
- It's gone--the catnip,
the kibble.

14:35.000 --> 14:36.666
He robbed us!
- Damn, he's good.

14:36.751 --> 14:39.002
- This is all your fault.
If you hadn't gotten

14:39.087 --> 14:41.212
So sidetracked by his
rippling, rock-hard,

14:41.298 --> 14:43.631
Well-defined abs,
we would be listening to

14:43.675 --> 14:45.091
Whale sounds at relaxicon!

14:45.176 --> 14:46.926
But now it's all about
your drama.

14:47.053 --> 14:48.595
I wish I were with
someone else.

14:48.680 --> 14:50.597
- Aah!

14:50.682 --> 14:52.557
- Well, well, well!

14:52.601 --> 14:54.767
Somebody's been a bad girl.

14:54.895 --> 14:56.185
- Ooh! It's me, it's me!

14:56.229 --> 14:57.604
Wait--stop!
What am I doing?

14:57.689 --> 14:58.688
Goodbye, shel!

14:58.732 --> 15:01.316
- [groans]

15:01.401 --> 15:02.817
- Nibbles! Ah, that's better.

15:02.903 --> 15:04.360
Or is it?

15:04.446 --> 15:05.695
- Nope.

15:05.780 --> 15:07.947
[fireworks popping]

15:08.033 --> 15:09.407
<i> - Can you point out</i>
<i> the dog</i>

15:09.451 --> 15:13.119
Who was intending to destroy
the boom factory?

15:13.163 --> 15:16.915
- That saint bernard there,
@mrfloofypants.

15:17.000 --> 15:18.917
- In hindsight,
it may have been a mistake

15:18.960 --> 15:20.293
To trust the senator's wife.

15:20.337 --> 15:22.795
- You thought you could
compete with this?

15:22.881 --> 15:24.589
Bllllll!

15:24.674 --> 15:27.634
- I've heard enough.
I hereby sentence you

15:27.719 --> 15:29.552
To ten dog years in prison.

15:29.596 --> 15:30.678
- Gulp.

15:30.764 --> 15:32.513
- And in the case of
hot or not,

15:32.599 --> 15:34.807
You're hot.

15:34.935 --> 15:37.060
All: [chanting]
chief! Chief!

15:37.145 --> 15:40.021
- My voice will never
be silenced.

15:40.065 --> 15:41.814
Never be--
[muffled speech]

15:41.900 --> 15:44.442
- Boo!
- Chief! Chief!

15:44.527 --> 15:47.236
Chief! Chief! Chief!

15:51.785 --> 15:54.077
- All right, chow time, chief.

15:59.960 --> 16:03.628
- Oh, man, I forgot about
my hunger strike!

16:03.672 --> 16:05.713
Ah, I'll start tomorrow.

16:05.757 --> 16:07.173
- You got a visitor.

16:07.217 --> 16:09.801
- Chief, old boy,
how are you holding up?

16:09.886 --> 16:11.928
- Uncle nathan?
- Not your uncle.

16:12.013 --> 16:14.681
Even in a drug-induced dream,
not your uncle.

16:14.766 --> 16:16.224
I work in the white dog house.

16:16.267 --> 16:19.185
The president would like
to see you...Personally.

16:19.270 --> 16:23.356
- The president of the
united steaks of america?

16:23.400 --> 16:24.857
- Oh, my god.

16:24.901 --> 16:27.151
It's your dream, chief.

16:27.195 --> 16:29.737
You could make yourself
a little smarter.

16:29.781 --> 16:32.782
<i> [uplifting music]</i>

16:32.826 --> 16:40.039
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:41.876 --> 16:43.668
- Madam president.

16:43.753 --> 16:45.962
- Honey? You're the president?

16:46.047 --> 16:48.423
- Of course! Who else
would it be--max?

16:48.508 --> 16:49.757
Walkies with me.

16:49.801 --> 16:51.050
<i> [bright music]</i>

16:51.136 --> 16:53.511
Chief, I need your help.
When I took office,

16:53.555 --> 16:55.722
I made a promise
to the american animal

16:55.765 --> 16:57.223
To eradicate the booms.

16:57.267 --> 16:59.017
And you've produced
an enormous,

16:59.102 --> 17:00.768
Well-formed movement.

17:00.854 --> 17:02.770
- Yeah. I make a lot of those.

17:02.814 --> 17:04.063
[fireworks popping]

17:04.107 --> 17:07.442
<i> [country western music]</i>

17:07.527 --> 17:09.736
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:09.821 --> 17:12.280
- What are you doing? We don't
have time for a pit stop.

17:12.365 --> 17:13.781
- Just wait out here
for two minutes.

17:13.867 --> 17:15.408
My ex lives here.
He'll hook us up

17:15.452 --> 17:17.827
With all the essentials--
food, money, oils.

17:17.871 --> 17:19.245
- Thanks, nibbles.

17:19.330 --> 17:21.706
For once, someone is solving
my problems.

17:21.750 --> 17:23.166
[sighs] ahh.

17:23.209 --> 17:25.543
- I ate his face!
We gotta get outta here!

17:25.628 --> 17:27.378
Go, go, go!

17:28.882 --> 17:30.757
- Unbelievable!
I'm stuck dealing with

17:30.800 --> 17:32.133
Someone else's
problems again.

17:32.177 --> 17:33.551
- You know I can hear you.

17:33.595 --> 17:35.303
I may be covered
in someone else's blood,

17:35.388 --> 17:37.889
But I still have feelings.
- Aah!

17:37.974 --> 17:40.349
Why is everyone but me
so annoying?

17:40.351 --> 17:41.726
- Aah!

17:41.770 --> 17:44.103
Hello, honey.
- Hello, honey!

17:44.147 --> 17:46.355
- Ahh...Perfect.
- Ahh...Perfect.

17:46.441 --> 17:49.984
<i> - ♪ we belong,</i>
<i> we belong together... ♪</i>

17:50.070 --> 17:53.654
<i> ["hail to the chief" plays]</i>

17:53.740 --> 17:56.783
- Help me finally do what
every president before me

17:56.826 --> 17:58.534
Has been afraid to.
- Hump the leg

17:58.620 --> 17:59.869
Of the lincoln memorial?

17:59.954 --> 18:02.038
- Please. I do that three times
before breakfast.

18:02.165 --> 18:03.956
I mean defeat big boom.

18:04.042 --> 18:06.167
- I'm your dog,
madam president.

18:06.252 --> 18:09.087
[crackling]
[gasps] what's that?

18:09.172 --> 18:11.047
It's me!
My tail is gonna explode!

18:11.132 --> 18:12.965
- [laughing]
- we've got a bark alarm

18:13.051 --> 18:15.051
Level 5 here with dotus.

18:15.095 --> 18:18.012
- Uncle nathan?
You set me up!

18:18.056 --> 18:20.640
- Not your uncle, and yes.

18:20.725 --> 18:23.017
- He used me to get to you.

18:23.061 --> 18:25.061
He's working for big boom!

18:25.063 --> 18:28.648
- Yes, I am.
See? That was smarter.

18:28.691 --> 18:30.608
But not smart enough.

18:30.693 --> 18:33.444
[chortling]

18:33.530 --> 18:36.114
- Get her outta here!
- We don't have time!

18:36.199 --> 18:38.324
- I'm on it!
- Ooh, that looks fun.

18:38.368 --> 18:40.868
Not the time--put it in my
calendar for tonight:

18:40.912 --> 18:42.370
If still alive, chase tail.

18:42.455 --> 18:43.663
- Got it!
- Now what?

18:43.706 --> 18:46.207
- I don't know.
I've never caught it before.

18:46.251 --> 18:47.375
- Let me help you.

18:47.544 --> 18:51.254
- No, no! I'm gonna
solve this problem myself.

18:51.339 --> 18:52.255
[grunts]

18:52.340 --> 18:54.340
Aah!

18:54.425 --> 18:58.302
- Looks like booms
are back on the menu, boys.

18:58.388 --> 19:00.096
- Aah!

19:01.766 --> 19:03.766
- Chief, you saved us!

19:03.852 --> 19:05.351
- And now I need your help.

19:05.395 --> 19:08.479
- To pass legislation
outlawing booms forever?

19:08.523 --> 19:09.814
- Oh, sure, but first...

19:09.899 --> 19:11.899
Help me get this racoon
outta my butt.

19:11.985 --> 19:13.860
[fireworks popping]

19:13.862 --> 19:17.062
[mellow music]

19:17.115 --> 19:19.365
- This is my favorite song.
- Mine too.

19:20.368 --> 19:22.160
Fried sweet potatoes
are my favorite.

19:22.245 --> 19:23.870
- Samesies.
- But maybe we should

19:23.913 --> 19:25.288
Slow down a bit.

19:25.331 --> 19:27.623
You get the best gas mileage
driving 65 to--

19:27.667 --> 19:31.335
- 75 miles per hour.
I know. I'm going 75.

19:32.130 --> 19:34.630
- Ooh. Going a little fast,
aren't we?

19:34.716 --> 19:36.048
- I know how to drive.

19:36.134 --> 19:37.967
- Ooh, she's in a mood.
- You don't even know.

19:38.052 --> 19:39.886
- I can hear you!

19:39.971 --> 19:41.804
- What are you doing--77?

19:41.890 --> 19:44.599
- What are you running from?
- Where's the sun block?

19:44.642 --> 19:46.142
- You're not a good girl.

19:46.227 --> 19:48.394
You're an average girl at best.
- Okay, got it.

19:48.438 --> 19:50.438
- Can we please stop?
- Let's just have some quiet.

19:50.565 --> 19:52.440
- Your peers have all
surpassed you.

19:52.567 --> 19:53.733
- Aah!

19:53.860 --> 19:55.318
[chatter continues]

19:55.361 --> 19:57.987
I can't take one more
minute of me!

19:58.031 --> 20:01.699
[chatter continues]

20:01.743 --> 20:04.076
Aah!

20:06.998 --> 20:08.414
Oh--
- wha--oh!

20:08.458 --> 20:10.416
I had the craziest dream.
- I had the craziest dream.

20:10.501 --> 20:12.084
- But I won't bore you with it.
- But I won't bore you with it.

20:12.170 --> 20:13.920
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

20:13.963 --> 20:16.047
- But I will tell you
what I learned from it.

20:16.132 --> 20:18.049
- Ooh! I'm listening.

20:18.134 --> 20:21.010
- I get what you were all
growly about earlier.

20:21.095 --> 20:23.471
I may not have giant
dream balls,

20:23.556 --> 20:25.348
But I have the power
to help myself.

20:25.433 --> 20:29.060
So from now on, I'm not gonna
bother you with my stuff.

20:29.145 --> 20:31.229
- No, no, no, please bother me.

20:31.314 --> 20:32.897
I'll spend as much time
as you want

20:32.941 --> 20:34.357
Talking about your problems.

20:34.442 --> 20:36.943
It's way less annoying
than talking to myself.

20:37.028 --> 20:39.820
- That's sweet, honey,
but this old dog can handle

20:39.864 --> 20:41.030
Whatever comes--
[pop]

20:41.115 --> 20:43.241
Aah! Why does this have to
be so scary?

20:43.326 --> 20:44.951
- It's okay, chief.
Shh, shh.

20:44.994 --> 20:46.661
President honey's got you.

20:46.746 --> 20:48.704
- Aw.

20:48.748 --> 20:50.164
Huh?

20:53.920 --> 20:56.295
- Oh, it was so exciting
to read this scene

20:56.339 --> 20:58.047
Because, as an actor,
it's really enjoyable

20:58.091 --> 21:00.800
To have all the lines
and all the screen time and--

21:00.885 --> 21:02.343
- Honey,
there's another of you!

21:02.428 --> 21:05.054
Where did she come from?
- They're both me.

21:05.139 --> 21:07.014
We shot the scenes
multiple times,

21:07.100 --> 21:09.183
And then they composited us--
- whoa!

21:09.269 --> 21:12.311
There's another one! So what
are they, clones or something?

21:12.397 --> 21:14.939
- No, it's a video effect.
- Ah--there's another clone!

21:15.024 --> 21:16.941
- Yeah, fine.
They're clones, chief.

21:17.026 --> 21:18.901
- Are you a clone?
- No.

21:18.987 --> 21:21.070
- That's exactly
what a clone would say.

21:21.197 --> 21:23.281
- I'm not a clone.
- Well, where are

21:23.324 --> 21:25.992
All the other clones?
- Fox put them all down

21:26.119 --> 21:28.828
After the shoot.
- Hmm. Probably would have

21:28.871 --> 21:30.997
Been easier
just to redraw you.

21:32.667 --> 21:34.667
[cheering]

21:35.169 --> 21:36.377
- That's nice,
jen and gabby.
